it of fear when i was younger i was motivated by this fire under me she explained it made me think oh my god where‚Äôs my life going to end up if i dont do something about itborn to an alcoholic mother and a father overwhelmed by the domestic situation mellon said she knew from a young age that she wanted to make her own money i never wanted to be dependent on my father or husband she told the summit audience i wanted to make my own decisionsthe british businesswoman left school without any qualifications and went to straight to work‚Äîa move she thinks has helped with her early success by the time i had founded jimmy choo i had a sound knowledge of the industry and working with luxury products from selling on the shop floor she saidmellons advice for those hoping to break into the fashion world is to just work‚Äîeven if its not your dream job or exactly what you want to do because you‚Äôll think of ideas and things will come to you when you‚Äôre being active it‚Äôs incredibly important just to workbut although the former vogue accessories editor did not go to college and described herself as terrible in school she does not recommend that her daughter yearold minty do the samei tell minty that an education is very important said mellon im very proud of her‚Äîshes pretty much a straighta student which i was not like at her age i always say you have to follow your passion and if you do then money will follow whatever mintys passionate about i support hercustomer servicesite mapprivacy policyadvertisingad choicesterms of useyour california privacy rightscareers  time inc all rights reservedall products and services featured are based solely on editorial selection fortune may receive compensation for some links to products and services on this website quotes delayed at least  minutes market data provided by interactive data etf and mutual fund data provided by morningstar inc dow jones terms  conditions httpwwwdjindexescommdsidxhtmltandcindexestandcshtml sp index data i