jimmy choo a luxury brand of shoes handbags and accessories she stepped down from the brand in november  after its acquisition by labelux in  mellon announced the creation of the tamara mellon brand offering a range of shoes handbags and accessories the brand launched in november  with a group of retail partners in the us and europe but filed for bankruptcy in  mellon resides in new york city and london with her daughter araminta minty mellon contents  early life  career  business difficulties  public and political activities  honours and awards  personal life  books  references early lifeedit mellon was born tamara yeardye in london on  july  she is the daughter of tom yeardye a stunt double for rock hudson and ann davis yeardye a former chanel model mellon is the eldest of three siblings her current surname stems from the time when she was married to matthew mellon an american businessman and member of the prominent mellon family in  mellons family relocated to beverly hills in a home next door to nancy sinatra mellon alternated between summers in california and the uk she attended two independent girls schools in berkshire‚Äîbrigidine convent school and heathfield st marys school‚Äîbefore attending finishing school in switzerland at the nowdefunct institut alpin videmanette careeredit mellon began her career at phyllis walters public relations mirabella and followed as accessories editor for british vogue in  recognizing the potential for development of highend designer accessories mellon approached bespoke shoemaker mr jimmy choo with the idea of launching a readytowear shoe company as cofounder of the jimmy choo company mellon secured funding from her father for the creation of her business and sourced factories in italy in addition she set up an office in italy to handle production quality control and shipping by  jimmy choo ltd had over  wholesale clients including harrods harvey nichols saks fifth avenue and bergdorf goodman and the collections accounted for over  of the production of several of these factories the first jimmy choo store on motcombe street in london was followed by stores in new york las vegas and beverly hills in april  jimmy choo ltd partnered with equinox luxury holdings ltd acquiring mr choo‚Äôs share of the readytowear business equinox‚Äôs chief executive robert bensoussan became ceo of jimmy choo ltd introducing handbag and small leather goods collections in november  with the company valued at ¬£ million hicks muse announced the majority acquisition of jimmy choo ltd the company subsequently opened jimmy choo stores in many cities including london sloane street  new bond street new york city beverly hills washington dc boston dallas moscow milan and hong kong and is distributed by select stores worldwide in  mellon appeared on the sunday times rich list where she was ranked as the st richest person in the uk with an estimated wealth of ¬£ million she was also ranked as the th richest woman in britain business difficultiesedit mellons shoe and apparel brand filed for bankruptcy under chapter  of the bankruptcy code in december  section  denotes that a business cannot repay its creditors and is entering a reorganisation strategy the filing states that the company has assets of between  million and  million and also has between  and  creditors who are owed between  million and  million she was forced to file under section  following pressure from angry investors predicted to lose approximately ¬£ million mellon was subsequently bailed out by american equity firm nea with a  million cash injection mellon is known to have previously criticised the private equity world as ‚Äúruthless opportunists who want to cash in‚Äù in january  mellons former backers filed an objection to the restructuring plans under american bankruptcy protection laws they stated that these plans allowed her her fianc√© and a fund to gain control of the new company leaving former financers with no repayment the objection includes accusations of mismanagement and abuse of the company including employing a life coach on the payroll and spending  on tickets to the met gala in new york the us department of justice also filed a formal objection mellon was recently quoted as saying you can write a guess in reference to her business plan in september  it was revealed that mellon is suing jimmy choo alleging that the company had blocked her from using luxury shoemakers in florence italy to produce her own line public and political activitiesedit mellon is a member of the new enterprise council a group of entrepreneurs who advise the conservative party uk on policies related to the needs of business on  november  she was named as a global trade envoy for britain by the british government she will have a roving brief to promote the country‚Äôs booming fashion industry overseas mellon has served on the board of directors for revlon since  she is also a patron of the elton john aids foundation honours and awardsedit in the  birthday honours mellon was appointed as an officer of the order of the british empire obe for services to the fashion industry on  november  mellon was presented with the fashion pioneer award at the women‚Äôs entrepreneurship day pioneer awards held in new york city at the united nations personal lifeedit in  mellon published the autobiography in my shoes in which she details her rise to success and her partnership with shoedesigner jimmy choo in an interview about the book with vanity fair she spoke of the challenges of designing shoes for the oscar season several media publications reported on the discussion in her book about her drug addiction issues specifically her problems with cocaine subsequent news coverage also focused on her stint in rehab party lifestyle and being fired from vogue magazine mellon‚Äôs battle with alcohol addiction is also well documented and she met her first husband matthew at alcoholics anonymous they later divorced and she wrote a number of articles about the dramatic details of her marriage referencing snorting her way through alpine ranges of cocaine in  she announced her engagement to michael ovitz in a magazine interview with hello it has since been revealed that ovitz is still married to his first wife judy she recently referred to the situation as ‚Äúcomplicated‚Äù booksedit mellon tamara william patrick  in my shoes a memoir new york portfoliopenguin isbn¬† oclc¬†¬† referencesedit  a b tamara mellon wwwvoguecouk¬†  a b c d e beeshyuan chang  october  tamara mellons next step the new york times¬†  official website at tamaramelloncom retrieved ¬†  susan berfield  october  jimmy choo cofounder tamara mellon puts on her revenge boots¬†  olivia lidbury  december  tamara mellon has filed for bankruptcy¬†  mulkerrins jane  april  emotional ties with entrepreneur and shoe designer tamara mellon daily mail london¬†  rich list search timesonlinecouk  womens rich list timesonlinecouk  lidbury olivia  december  tamara mellon has filed for bankruptcy the telegraph¬†  milligan laura  december  tamara mellon files for bankruptcy vogue¬†  sunderland ruth  december  how the highliving jimmy choo shoe queen crashed to earth shes david camerons trade ambassador but theres a humiliating new episode in tamara mellons life as her firm goes bankrupt daily mail¬†  evans peter  december  tamara mellon thrown lifeline the sunday times¬†  sabharwal veebs  december  tamara mellon saved from drowning retail gazette¬†  evans peter  january  mellon mauled the sunday times¬†  a b c pavia will  february  don‚Äôt mess with tamara mellon the sunday times¬†  tamara mellon jimmy choo cofounder sues the famed footwear company ‚Äî the fashion law thefashionlawcom  retrieved ¬†    chapman james  november  jimmy choo queen tamara mellon is unveiled as britains new ¬£m trade envoy daily mail london¬†  tamara mellon forbes¬†  revlon website phxcorporateirnet retrieved ¬†  elton john aids foundation patrons ejafcom retrieved ¬†  no  the london gaz